description: "The London-based cartographer Herman Moll (1654?–1732) created this map of Asia in the early 18th century. There are five insets showing Asian trading cities, including of the ports of Batavia (Jakarta) and Bantam (Banten) in western Java."
title: "Charte   von   Ost-Indien   und   den   angrolntzenden   Laendern   ...   Geographi   Mr.   Herman   Moll   ...   "
